  <Subject Subject_ID="300055593">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300055588</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>property (legal concept) [300055588], property and related concepts [300168484], legal concepts [300055547], social science concepts [300239103], Associated Concepts (hierarchy name) [300055126], Associated Concepts Facet [300264086]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Movable works or built works, or parts of works, having archaeological or ethnological value to a particular culture, often subject to export restrictions of the particular country where they were created or discovered. Includes property having significant importance to the cultural heritage of a people, such as monuments of architecture, art or history, whether religious or secular; archaeological sites; groups of buildings which, as a whole, are of historical or artistic interest, works of art, artifacts, manuscripts, books and other objects of artistic, historical or archaeological interest; as well as scientific collections and important collections of books or archives.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046445/Convention on Cultural Property Implementation Act (1987)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000098414/Hague Convention for the Protection of Cultural Property (1954-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Parte o el todo de un objeto de interés arqueológico o un objeto de interés etnológico el que fue descubierto por primera vez y está sujeto al control de exportación por el estado.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een (deel van een) object van archeologische of etnologische waarde dat is ontdekt in een land, en waarvoor exportbeperkingen gelden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>意指一件部分或整體具有考古價值或民族學價值的物品，最早發現於《世界文化與自然遺產保護公約》的締約國境內，且由該國控制這項物品的出口。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
